The paper also discusses the equivalence or reducibility of these problems to Hidden Subgroup, which involves computational complexity and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions nonadaptive program checkers, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with permutation groups, which could fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
